            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost">Hic</supplied> iace&amp;lt;t=I&amp;gt; Dulcitius peleger <note>sic</note> civis <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>enus qui vixit annus <note>sic</note> XXV <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>mens</abbr><ex>es</ex></expan></supplied> VI d&amp;lt;ep=II&amp;gt;ositus in pace n&amp;lt;e=I&amp;gt;o<lb break="no" n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">fitus sub <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ie</ex></expan></supplied> VI Idus Augustas co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulatu</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>omino</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>ostro</ex></expan> Arca</supplied>dio &amp;lt;e=I&amp;gt;t Bauton&amp;lt;e=I&amp;gt; <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>iro</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissimo</ex></expan> 
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>2 aneinanderpassende Fragmente; Fundjahre: 1922 und 1923. Die Platte war in ein Mosaik im Mittelschiff nahe der Tür eingelassen. 2 aneinanderpassende Fragmente erhalten. (B): Brøndsted; ILJug: Kleinere Leseabweichungen.</p>
